						<summary>

						<p>In the verandah of the same cave, below two images.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sundara-pāṇḍyadēva (Māṟavarman Sundara pāṇḍya: I Year 8: 1223-24 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This, much-damaged record, describes the king as <hi rend="italic">Śōṇāḍu-vaḻaṅgiyaruḷiya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record the gift of lands and levies in a place (name lost) to god, Āḷuḍaiyapiḻḻaiyār in the temple of [Tē]nāṟṟu-Nāyakar in Tiru[kkuṉṟakkuḍi] one of the villages irrigated by (the river) Tēnāṟu, in Kēraḻasiṅgavaḻanāḍu, probably by Gaṇḍaṉ Amudagaṇḍaṉ of Niyamam.</p>						

						</summary>
